File: The Public Servants Association says workers are already carrying the burden of the high cost of living which is aggravated by rising electricity costs and rising prices of goods. JOHANNESBURG - The Public Servants Association is slamming a government proposal to review the 2020 wage agreement. The union says public servants cannot afford to sacrifice their salary increments. READ: PSA warns of more troubles for Busisiwe Mkhwebane It says workers are already carrying the burden of the high cost of living which is aggravated by rising electricity costs and rising prices of goods. The PSA is one of the country's largest public service unions with over 240,000 members. WATCH: Looking at SA's skyrocketing debt The union says the government must stop making public servants scapegoats and deal with its own wasteful expenditure.